  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nTruffle config provides a nice feature to silence compilation logs. If I add:\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  quiet:  true\r\n}\r\n```\r\nTo my config and run `truffle compile`, this works as expected. But when I run `truffle test`, truffle still outputs all compilation logs. I expected `truffle test` to also respect my quiet config.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n- Add the `quiet` flag to the config\r\n- Run `truffle test`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expected Truffle to silence the compile logs.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nFull output logs of my project when running `truffle test`:\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/sbrichards/e057c51042bf509082bba35cb95d5498\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS Mojave 10.14.5.\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache\r\n```\r\n$ truffle version\r\nTruffle v5.0.21 (core: 5.0.21)\r\nSolidity - 0.4.24 (solc-js)\r\nNode v10.13.0\r\nWeb3.js v1.0.0-beta.37\r\n```\r\n",
